    "created_at": "2016-03-31T05:38:46Z",
    "updated_at": "2016-03-31T05:44:38Z",
    "body": "I just tested Atom 1.6.1 on a Windows machine that has two G-Sync enabled monitors, and I'm still seeing this performance problem.\n\nI've tested the following applications that use Electron, and they are all exhibiting the same behavior:\n- Atom 1.6.1\n- VS Code 0.10.11\n- GitHub Desktop 3.0.16.0\n- Slack 2.0.3\n\nI don't have this problem in Chrome itself, currently running Version 49.0.2623.110 m (64-bit).\n\nSome additional info about the machine:\n- Windows 10 Version 1511 (OS Build 10586.164)\n- NVIDIA GeForce  GTX 980 Ti using the 364.72 drivers\n- Monitors: Two Asus ROG Swift PG279Q\n"
  },
